<item>
            <title>[DOXIA-131] HtmlTools.encodeId makes id lower case</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DOXIA-131</link>
                <project id="12317230" key="DOXIA">Maven Doxia (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HtmlTools.encodeId uses Character.toLowerCase to convert its argument to lower case. I don&apos;t see the reason for that since upper case characters are legal in id&apos;s (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/types.html#type-name&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/types.html#type-name&lt;/a&gt; ). In particular, it&apos;s a problem with anchors/links in the xhtml sink (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DOXIA-47&quot; title=&quot;APT - local named anchors in apt text are not created properly.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DOXIA-47&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DOXIA-47&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ), especially if we want to create anchors from section names, to maintain backward compatibility with m1. Is there a special reason for the toLowerCase or can we remove it?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12801427">DOXIA-131</key>
            <summary>HtmlTools.encodeId makes id lower case</summary>
